To decode this key, I copy and pasted the private key into the online decoder. From there, I looked at the first several bytes knowing the structure of the DER headers. The rest, until a new section started, was the actual value. 


The first element is a sequence.

There are a total of 9 integers:

1. Version. 0x00
At offset 4, there are 3 bytes, 02 01 00. 02 signifies the identifier as an Integer, 01 is the length, and 00 is the actual value.
 
2. Modulus (n) 



The bytes used are at offset 7. With 4 bytes of DER headers and 385 bytes of data.

The DER 4 bytes are 02 82 01 81, where 02 signifies it is an integer. 82 alerts us that the length will be encoded in the next 2 bytes, which end up being 0x0181, or 385. 

3. PublicExponent 65537 . E
At offset 396, there are 5 bytes used, 2 bytes for DER octets and 3 bytes for the values. The first byte, 02, signals that this is an integer. The next byte, 03, signals the length of the coming value decoded. Thus, 01 00 01 becomes 65537.

4. PrivateExponent  D 

At offset 401, there are at 4 bytes of DER headers and 385 bytes of values. The 4 bytes of DER encoding are 02 82 01 81, where 02 tags it as an integer, 82 signifies the length of the length encoding is 2, and 01 81 signifies the length of the value is 0x181, or 385. 


5. Prime1 

At an offset of 790, this integer is coded in 3 bytes of DER headers and 193 bytes of value. The DER encoding is 02 81 C1, where 02 specifies that this is an integer, 81 specifies that the length of the length encoding is 1 byte, and then C1 is the actual length, which is 193 in decimal.

6. Prime2 

At an offset of 984, this integer is coded in 3 bytes of DER headers and 193 bytes of value. The DER encoding is 02 81 C1, where 02 specifies that this is an integer, 81 specifies that the length of the length encoding is 1 byte, and then C1 is the actual length, which is 193 in decimal.

7. Exponent 1 


At an offset of 1182, this integer is coded in 3 bytes of DER headers and 193 bytes of value. The DER encoding is 02 81 C0, where 02 specifies that this is an integer, 81 specifies that the length of the length encoding is 1 byte, and then C1 is the actual length of the value, which is 192 in decimal.


8. Exponent 2 


At an offset of 1377, this integer is coded in 3 bytes of DER headers and 193 bytes of value. The DER encoding is 02 81 C0, where 02 specifies that this is an integer, 81 specifies that the length of the length encoding is 1 byte, and then C1 is the actual length of the value, which is 192 in decimal.

9. Coefficient 

At an offset of 1572, this integer is coded in 3 bytes of DER headers and 193 bytes of value.
